The paper discusses a system for efficient XPath search over compressed text and tree indexes, which is relevant to information retrieval (IR) and database (DB) systems. The use of tree automata suggests a connection to formal language theory and computational complexity (CC). The system also involves data structures and algorithms (DS) for storing and querying the indexes, and compression techniques (DL) for reducing memory consumption.
